Diagnosis. Large-sized deltocephaline leafhoppers with red markings and claval veins outlined with grayish pigmentation; Forewing with veins M and CuA confluent for a short distance near the base of the wing, vein 2 A in the clavus sinuate and confluent with 1 A; subgenital plate without macrosetae and male segment X with falcate process arising anteroventrally (
Fig. 17
).
